title: Abilene, Kansas
summary: Abilene (pronounced /ˈæbɪliːn/)[8] is a city in and the county seat of Dickinson County, Kansas, United States.[9]  As of the 2020 census, the population of the city was 6,460.[4][5]  It is home of The Dwight D. Eisenhower Presidential Library and Museum and the Greyhound Hall of Fame.
